    "128903391": {
      "title": "Mozambique: A new geological framework for hydrocarbon exploration",
      "abstract": "Modern exploration for hydrocarbons began in Mozambique in 1981. The newly-acquired data augment those gathered in the territory prior to political independence in 1975, and provide a basis for an updated appraisal of the country's hydrocarbon potential. This is concentrated in the marginal Mozambique and Rovuma Basins, whose development was initiated during the break-up of Gondwana. A \"fit\" for Madagascar against coastal Tanzania and Somalia is accepted as representing the region's early plate-tectonic configuration."
